mem:constraint-01kjcyjgszs18b9h4jg7h3xpfj a mem:Constraint ;
    mem:content "Consensus/multisig gotcha for config graph: commit validity rules (validator set/threshold) used to validate a proposed commit at t must come from already-committed state (effectively config as-of t-1), not from config mutations inside the same commit; otherwise a commit could authorize itself by changing validator set/threshold in its own payload. Config can declare consensus parameters, but validation must treat them as lagging state." ;
    mem:tag "commit-validation" ;
    mem:tag "config-graph" ;
    mem:tag "consensus" ;
    mem:tag "gotcha" ;
    mem:tag "multisig" ;
    mem:tag "raft" ;
    mem:tag "tendermint" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-26T12:25:27.104151+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:constraint-01km6xq65xn4dzghwnf4wc5ax6 a mem:Constraint ;
    mem:content "Overlay ops for `BinaryCursor` overlay merge must be (1) sorted by the cursor's `RunSortOrder` and (2) deduplicated by `FactKeyV3` before merging, otherwise duplicate ops for the same fact can cause duplicate outputs or incorrect suppression. Dedup should be deterministic: if multiple ops share the same `FactKeyV3` at the same max `t`, prefer `retract` over `assert` (final state = not present) to avoid nondeterminism from `sort_unstable` tie ordering." ;
    mem:tag "binary-cursor" ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "dedup" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "sort" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:severity "must" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_cursor.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/types.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T00:46:28.541390+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:decision-01kjtd4ddbk45wadcafd8tfea7 a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "When a novelty overlay is present, the fast POST leaflet-skipping operators (`PredicateGroupCountFirstsOperator`, `PredicateObjectCountFirstsOperator`) can stay on the fast base path and apply an exact overlay delta by translating overlay flakes to `OverlayOp` IDs and simulating per-fact state transitions in time order. We infer initial presence from the first op (first retract => existed pre-overlay) and adjust counts on assert/retract transitions; this avoids falling back to `range_with_overlay` for overlays." ;
    mem:tag "count" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
    mem:tag "novelty" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "post" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_group_count_firsts.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-03T17:50:01.131764+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Preserve the leaflet FIRST-skipping performance while still producing correct results under novelty, given the invariant that overlay retractions only target facts that existed at the time." ;
    mem:alternatives "Always fall back when overlay/policy/history is active; use BinaryCursor merge for overlay even in fast-path; do per-assert base existence checks." .

mem:decision-01kkm7rvsg9ckza0rssnhd9h7t a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "Implemented SPARQL DESCRIBE by lowering it to a CONSTRUCT-style graph expansion that returns outgoing triples for described resources: bind a synthetic `?__describe` (via VALUES for explicit IRIs and/or a subquery over the WHERE clause), then match `?__describe ?p ?o` and output as `QueryOutput::Construct`. This avoids full-graph scans when no targets bind (empty VALUES guard) and is benchmark-friendly (BSBM query 9). Also updated tracked query formatting (view + dataset) and CLI `fluree query` to auto-format CONSTRUCT/DESCRIBE as JSON-LD instead of SPARQL-JSON (which would error)." ;
    mem:tag "benchmark" ;
    mem:tag "cli" ;
    mem:tag "construct" ;
    mem:tag "describe" ;
    mem:tag "formatting" ;
    mem:tag "lowering" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/query/sparql.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/reference/compatibility.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/dataset_query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/commands/query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/lower/describe.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/lower/mod.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-13T18:36:34.992265+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "DESCRIBE semantics are implementation-defined; outgoing-triple expansion is simple, fast, and matches BSBM usage while preserving modifier semantics via a subquery." ;
    mem:alternatives "Per-resource secondary queries (slower), include incoming triples too (more expensive output), single-query join without subquery (LIMIT/OFFSET semantics wrong)." .

mem:decision-01kkmfs0sktrfn7ny36wzmwv9n a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "Added RDF/XML output for SPARQL CONSTRUCT/DESCRIBE via API `FormatterConfig::rdf_xml()` + server `Accept: application/rdf+xml`. Implementation uses construct template instantiation into `fluree_graph_ir::Graph` (shared helper `instantiate_construct_graph`) and a minimal RDF/XML serializer that requires predicate IRIs to be QName-splittable (last '#' or '/' and NCName local). Server rejects RDF/XML for SELECT/ASK, tracked, proxy-mode, and identity-scoped SPARQL paths; supports it for ledger-scoped SPARQL, including dataset-clause queries." ;
    mem:tag "accept" ;
    mem:tag "construct" ;
    mem:tag "describe" ;
    mem:tag "formatting" ;
    mem:tag "rdfxml" ;
    mem:tag "server" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/api/headers.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/format/config.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/format/construct.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/format/rdf_xml.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/extract/headers.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/routes/query.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-13T20:56:28.723996+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "BSBM testdriver requests RDF/XML for DESCRIBE. Implementing a full general RDF/XML QName mapping is complex; current serializer targets typical benchmark IRIs with safe local names and fails fast otherwise." .

mem:decision-01kkpnby15haz8aprhpxjdz4mb a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "BSBM explore outliers: Q3/Q4/Q5 shapes identified. Q3 is star + OPTIONAL{ feature2 + label } with FILTER(!bound(?testVar)) which acts like an anti-join (products matching base constraints but NOT having a specific feature). Q4 is UNION of two star-shaped branches with ORDER BY + OFFSET + LIMIT and SELECT DISTINCT, which forces broader materialization/sort when duplicates can arise across branches. Q5 is a similarity query joining ProductXYZ features to other products via shared feature plus numeric range filters; naive execution can spend most time in the shared-feature join and candidate expansion before numeric filters reduce rows." ;
    mem:tag "benchmark" ;
    mem:tag "bsbm" ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "planner" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "benchmarks/bsbm/bsbmtools-0.2/queries/explore/query3.txt" ;
    mem:artifactRef "benchmarks/bsbm/bsbmtools-0.2/queries/explore/query4.txt" ;
    mem:artifactRef "benchmarks/bsbm/bsbmtools-0.2/queries/explore/query5.txt" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/operator_tree.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-14T17:12:40.229851+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Provides concrete starting points for targeted generic optimizations (anti-join rewrite, UNION branch planning, semijoin/candidate generation for shared-feature joins) before deeper implementation work." .

mem:decision-01kkvnqthjzjc1h40rx76gpq99 a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "SPARQL OPTIONAL semantics: treat `OPTIONAL { A . B }` as a single conjunctive left-join block (no partial binding when only some triples in the block match). Updated integration test accordingly by renaming `sparql_optional_multi_pattern_allows_partial_binding` to `sparql_optional_multi_pattern_requires_conjunctive_match` and changing expected results to all-unbound optional vars when either triple is missing." ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "tests" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_sparql.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/lower/pattern.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-16T15:55:22.034971+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Align behavior with SPARQL algebra semantics and earlier OPTIONAL lowering fix (keep multi-triple OPTIONAL as one Pattern::Optional group). Prevents incorrect partial bindings that break NOT EXISTS / !bound() patterns (e.g., BSBM Q3)." ;
    mem:alternatives "Keep old behavior by splitting multi-triple OPTIONAL into multiple independent OPTIONALs (non-standard)" .

mem:decision-01km88js2zfk0b5465psvc8c35 a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "Fast-path PSOT cursor builders and dependent operators now prefer correctness-preserving fallback over hard failure when novelty overlay translation to V3 IDs fails. `build_psot_cursor_for_predicate` (and the group variant) returns `Ok(None)` if overlay flakes can't be translated (e.g., missing/stale DictNovelty or unsupported value types), and callers treat `None` as \"fast path unavailable\" and run their provided fallback operators instead of returning an internal error. This keeps the hot path unchanged when translation succeeds and avoids silently wrong results under novelty edge cases." ;
    mem:tag "binary-cursor" ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "dict-novelty" ;
    mem:tag "fallback" ;
    mem:tag "fast-path" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "psot" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_group_count_firsts.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_path_common.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_property_path_plus_count_all.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_transitive_path_plus_count_all.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_union_star_count_all.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T13:15:32.831834+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Database correctness must not depend on flawless overlay translation; when overlay cannot be mapped into binary ID space, the system should choose a slower correct path rather than erroring or producing partial results." ;
    mem:alternatives "Hard-fail the query on translation error; always disable fast paths whenever overlay is present" .

mem:decision-01kmqh7wfsc15dzw6fvkesyza8 a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "Untyped numeric equality on the V3 binary path now uses a loose encoded prefilter (match by o_key, omit o_type) plus decoded-value equality, instead of forcing `FlakeValue::Long` to `OType::XSD_INTEGER`. This was needed because txn-meta `db:t` values can be stored as `xsd:long`, and exact `o_type` filtering in `binary_range_eq_v3`/`BinaryScanOperator` could miss valid matches." ;
    mem:tag "binary-range" ;
    mem:tag "binary-scan" ;
    mem:tag "commit-t" ;
    mem:tag "datatype" ;
    mem:tag "integer-family" ;
    mem:tag "numeric" ;
    mem:tag "query-correctness" ;
    mem:tag "txn-meta" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/range.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_range.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-27T11:35:29.529039+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Reuse the existing decoded equality semantics instead of reimplementing datatype-family fanout separately in each binary caller." ;
    mem:alternatives "Predicate-only decode/filter in resolve_t_to_commit_id, stats-driven multi-scan per datatype" .

mem:decision-01knptda6efn6yhxj44hcnvsxh a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "Raw nameservice commit-head publication was removed from the public `Publisher` trait and connection convenience APIs. Commit-head changes now go through `RefPublisher`: normal transaction/merge/rebase paths use `compare_and_set_ref` with the previously validated head, rebase replay uses `fast_forward_commit`, and bulk import tracks the last published `RefValue` so periodic checkpoints CAS against the last published head instead of the immediately previous commit." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "compare-and-set" ;
    mem:tag "import" ;
    mem:tag "merge" ;
    mem:tag "nameservice" ;
    mem:tag "rebase" ;
    mem:tag "refpublisher" ;
    mem:tag "transact" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/import.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/merge.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/rebase.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-connection/src/aws.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-nameservice/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/commit.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-08T15:12:11.982180+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Avoid exposing blind monotonic head publication that can silently no-op on stale writes; require explicit CAS semantics so callers observe conflicts clearly." ;
    mem:alternatives "Keep publish_commit and verify after write, or deprecate only wrapper APIs while leaving the raw trait public." .

mem:fact-01kjjd0b982vvxq7kxvn9bs90s a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Historical time-travel views must attach a BinaryRangeProvider when loading a BinaryIndexStore. `LedgerSnapshot::from_root_bytes()` produces a metadata-only snapshot with `range_provider=None`, so `Fluree::load_graph_db_at_t()` needs to set `LedgerSnapshot.range_provider = Some(BinaryRangeProvider::new(store, dict_novelty))` after loading the binary store; otherwise range-based operators can error with: \"binary-only db has no range_provider attached — load and attach BinaryIndexStore before queries\"." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "binaryrangeprovider" ;
    mem:tag "bugfix" ;
    mem:tag "historical-view" ;
    mem:tag "range-provider" ;
    mem:tag "time-travel" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/fluree_ext.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/db.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/range.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T15:13:52.424054+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjjmk1nva80w5cj3ey87asnj a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Global LRU \"leaflet cache\" (single memory budget):\n- Implementation: `fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs` (`LeafletCache`) uses a single `moka::sync::Cache` (TinyLFU) shared across decoded entry types (R1/R2 leaflet regions + dict leaves + BM25 leaflets + vector shards). One pool = one cache budget.\n- Budget control: `FLUREE_LEAFLET_CACHE_BYTES` (default 8 GiB) sets the max bytes for the cache.\n- Wiring: enabled by default in `fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs` (`LedgerManagerConfig::default()` creates `LeafletCache::with_max_bytes(...)`), and used by `BinaryIndexStore` load paths when ledger caching is on.\n- Note: Region 3 (history journal) is intentionally never cached (cold path)." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet-cache" ;
    mem:tag "lru" ;
    mem:tag "moka" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T17:26:25.211748+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjjn8kspr3gnkcsmq9t1fsvf a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "API-level ledger-info caching uses the global unified LeafletCache (TinyLFU) so it shares the single memory budget (FLUREE_LEAFLET_CACHE_BYTES, default 8 GiB).\n\nCache key: xxh3_128 of (ledger_id, commit_t, index_t, realtime_property_details, include_property_datatypes, graph selector, context JSON hash).\nValue: serialized JSON bytes (Arc<[u8]>). Cache hit returns parsed JSON without recomputing novelty-merged stats. Naturally busts when commit_t or index_t changes." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet-cache" ;
    mem:tag "ledger-info" ;
    mem:tag "moka" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "tinylfu" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_info.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T17:38:11.894884+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjjswkfg62ratezvpdchg30h a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Leaflet region decode behavior (read-side): `BinaryCursor` decodes Region 1 first and only decodes Region 2 (dt/t/lang/i) when (a) the caller requested metadata via `need_region2` AND there is at least one Region-1 match in that leaflet, OR (b) overlay merge is active, OR (c) time-travel replay is active. Region 1 and Region 2 are cached independently in the unified `LeafletCache` (TinyLFU) so caching R1 does not imply caching R2. Region 3 (history journal) is decoded only for time-travel and is intentionally never cached; however leaf files are currently fetched/mmap'd as whole objects, so Region 3 bytes still contribute to leaf download size for non-history queries." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "region1" ;
    mem:tag "region2" ;
    mem:tag "region3" ;
    mem:tag "time-travel" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/format/leaflet.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_cursor.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T18:59:01.232091+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjp8g2s9pfh64sbx1crx42d8 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Query API layering in fluree-db-api:\n- query_connection() is the request-boundary entrypoint: parses dataset spec/options, chooses execution model, applies policy and config defaults. Uses GraphDb for single-ledger (including time travel) and DataSetDb for multi-ledger union.\n- query(&GraphDb, ...) is the stable single-ledger API: load a GraphDb once via db()/db_at_t()/db_at(), run many queries.\n- DataSetDb supports history/changes via history_range: Option<(from_t,to_t)>." ;
    mem:tag "api-layering" ;
    mem:tag "dataset" ;
    mem:tag "fluree-db-api" ;
    mem:tag "graphdb" ;
    mem:tag "history" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "query-connection" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/query/connection.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/dataset.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/dataset_query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/fluree_ext.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/query.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-02T03:12:02.857222+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjt5bpzz5aqvv93syafs18m1 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Fast GROUP BY ?o COUNT(?s) top-k optimization is now generic for any bound predicate in POST: `PredicateGroupCountFirstsOperator` scans leaflets using uncompressed per-leaflet FIRST (p,o) metadata and uses boundary-equality (FIRST(i)==FIRST(i+1)) to add `row_count` without decoding. It consults `StatsView::get_graph_property(g_id,p_id)` at open-time: if exactly one datatype and it maps to a reserved dt_id (and is not langString), it avoids decoding Region2 entirely and emits `EncodedLit` with constant dt_id/lang_id=0; otherwise it falls back to decoding Region2 and groups by (o_kind,o_key,dt_id,lang_id) for correctness." ;
    mem:tag "count" ;
    mem:tag "datatype" ;
    mem:tag "group-by" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
    mem:tag "optimization" ;
    mem:tag "post-index" ;
    mem:tag "region2" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "statsview" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/operator_tree.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_group_count_firsts.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-03T15:34:11.711499+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjtbbfnpgec8tk0zqjeg7sb8 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Added POST leaflet-skipping fast path for bound-object COUNT queries: `PredicateObjectCountFirstsOperator` answers `SELECT (COUNT(?s) AS ?c) WHERE { ?s <p> <o> }` (single triple, bound predicate+object, no dt/lang constraint, no GROUP BY) by scanning POST leaflets using uncompressed FIRST (p,o) metadata and boundary-equality to add `row_count` without decoding; falls back to decoding Region1 for partial leaflets. Wired via `detect_predicate_object_count` in `execute/operator_tree.rs`, and preserves existing loose semantics when `tp.dtc` is None (ignores dt/lang)." ;
    mem:tag "count" ;
    mem:tag "fast-path" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
    mem:tag "optimization" ;
    mem:tag "post-index" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/operator_tree.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_group_count_firsts.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-03T17:18:55.670244+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kkmfektg8ednzhkrsh09dck4 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "SPARQL Results XML (`application/sparql-results+xml`) is now supported via `FormatterConfig::sparql_xml()` in fluree-db-api. Server ledger-scoped SPARQL endpoint honors `Accept: application/sparql-results+xml` for non-tracked, non-identity, non-proxy SPARQL queries by returning SPARQL Results XML (SELECT/ASK only). CONSTRUCT/DESCRIBE are rejected for this format. Implementation lives in `fluree-db-api/src/format/sparql_xml.rs` and is wired through `format_results_string(_async)`; server wiring in `fluree-db-server/src/routes/query.rs` with header helper `FlureeHeaders::wants_sparql_results_xml()`." ;
    mem:tag "accept" ;
    mem:tag "content-negotiation" ;
    mem:tag "formatting" ;
    mem:tag "server" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "xml" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
