    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T01:55:15.936809+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01km5nyf5803na09n60d6z8j30 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Binary-scan bound-term normalization depends on BinaryIndexStore namespace codes: extract_bound_terms re-encodes Sid via store.sid_to_iri(sid) then store.encode_iri(&iri). If store lacks a namespace code (new namespace from post-index commits), sid_to_iri drops the prefix (empty fallback) and encode_iri falls back to EMPTY code 0, causing bound filters to miss.\n\nMitigation: augment BinaryIndexStore namespace table with snapshot's namespace_codes when new deltas are applied." ;
    mem:tag "binary-scan" ;
    mem:tag "namespace" ;
    mem:tag "novelty" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "prefix-trie" ;
    mem:tag "query-bug" ;
    mem:tag "reload" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger/loading.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-ledger/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T13:11:24.072938+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01km5pmwnsym5zz3vgpyz4k1rt a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Fix for 'new namespace after binary index attached' bound-query bug: `BinaryScanOperator` now keeps bound pattern SIDs in *snapshot* namespace space for overlay matching, and constructs persisted binary filters by decoding those SIDs to full IRIs via `LedgerSnapshot::decode_sid` then re-encoding via `BinaryIndexStore::encode_iri`. This avoids depending on the store's namespace table being updated after commit deltas, while preserving correct filtering when store namespace codes differ from snapshot (e.g., after rebuild). Regression test: `fluree-db-api/tests/it_namespace_new_after_index.rs`." ;
    mem:tag "binary-scan" ;
    mem:tag "namespace" ;
    mem:tag "novelty" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "prefix-trie" ;
    mem:tag "regression-test" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_namespace_new_after_index.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T13:23:38.809931+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01km6e7s84vcmvhrxvtcwgfkka a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`IriCompactor` only auto-derives fallback prefixes when the provided `ParsedContext` is non-empty (has terms/@vocab/@base). If you want compact display IRIs without a user-supplied @context, pass a synthetic context with well-known prefixes so fallback derivation activates for user namespaces too (e.g., `IriCompactor::with_fallback_prefixes(namespace_codes)` pattern). Also ensure any emitted `@context` matches the exact prefixes actually used for compaction (handle collisions/unique suffixes)." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "commit-detail" ;
    mem:tag "context" ;
    mem:tag "iri-compaction" ;
    mem:tag "json-ld" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/format/iri.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_commit_builder.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T20:15:55.140833+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01km81d85z7rfdckve3wqwtszx a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Graph crawl formatting overlay gotcha: in binary_range_eq_v3, overlay flake→V3 translation can fail when DictNovelty is uninitialized (novelty-only strings/subjects unresolvable). Previously failed translations were WARN-logged and DROPPED, causing properties to disappear when a translated retract suppresses base row but asserted novelty value fails translation.\n\nFix: keep failed translations as raw Flakes, run post-pass merging raw overlay with cursor output, resolve per-fact lifecycles (latest t wins, tie prefers retract), drop retracts, then apply RangeOptions." ;
    mem:tag "binary-range" ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "dict-novelty" ;
    mem:tag "graph-crawl" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/format/graph_crawl.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_range.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T11:10:11.647303+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01km8qneeknvq50y6dvm459rne a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Graph crawl formatter previously only included `@id` when `*` was used (or `@id` explicitly selected) at that crawl level, which dropped identity for nested ref sub-selects like `{ \"schema:isBasedOn\": [\"schema:name\"] }`, producing `{ \"schema:name\": ... }` without `@id`.\n\nFix: `fluree-db-api/src/format/graph_crawl.rs` now always includes `@id` for nested expansions (`current_depth > 0`), while keeping root-level behavior unchanged unless `*` or explicit `@id` is requested.\n\nRegression test: `jsonld_graph_crawl_nested_subselect_includes_id` in `fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_jsonld_basic.rs` (was failing, now passes)." ;
    mem:tag "@id" ;
    mem:tag "formatter" ;
    mem:tag "graph-crawl" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "regression-test" ;
    mem:tag "subselect" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T17:39:08.884534+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmbj3527qd54y3whzjhwc4bg a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "SPARQL UPDATE WHERE now supports full GraphPattern (same as SELECT): OPTIONAL, FILTER, UNION, VALUES, BIND, subselects+aggregates. In fluree-db-transact, parsed WHERE stored as Txn.sparql_where with prologue+pattern, deferred until staging where it's lowered via fluree_db_sparql::lower_sparql with LedgerSnapshot as encoder. stage::execute_where handles both JSON-LD unresolved patterns and SPARQL-lowered patterns via same query engine.\n\nTests: it_transact_conditional.rs (JSON-LD with subquery aggregate), server integration.rs (SPARQL UPDATE with subquery+MAX+BIND)." ;
    mem:tag "aggregate" ;
    mem:tag "bind" ;
    mem:tag "max" ;
    mem:tag "query-engine" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "stage" ;
    mem:tag "subquery" ;
    mem:tag "transact" ;
    mem:tag "update" ;
