mem:fact-01kmgg192p7hnveqckgqxyakz7 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Iceberg Direct catalog flow: in server-side scan paths, create the S3 storage client once and share it (e.g., Arc<Storage>) with SendDirectCatalogClient; avoid moving the storage into the catalog client and then re-creating storage just to read metadata/manifests. Use Arc::clone(&storage) for the catalog and pass &*storage to planners/readers." ;
    mem:tag "aws" ;
    mem:tag "direct-catalog" ;
    mem:tag "gotcha" ;
    mem:tag "iceberg" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "s3" ;
    mem:tag "storage" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_source/r2rml.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-iceberg/src/catalog/direct.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-iceberg/src/catalog/mod.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-24T17:59:43.446602+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmqg0w83yereh4ypzr7eqv8b a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "FLI3 leaf files can legally contain more than 255 leaflets because the format stores `leaflet_count` as u32 and V3 leaf assembly flushes leaves by `leaf_target_rows`, not by leaflet count; POST/PSOT segmentation on `p_id` transitions and OPST segmentation on `o_type` transitions can therefore create many tiny leaflets in one leaf. Read-side cached query paths still key V3 batches by `leaflet_idx: u8`, so when a query scans a leaf whose 257th leaflet is reached it fails with `leaflet index 256 exceeds u8::MAX` (or query-side `leaflet idx exceeds u8`)." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "bug" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "v3-cursor" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/format/leaf.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_cursor.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-27T11:14:11.331131+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmqhh9n5qtsnjt3f7eq8xf3p a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`fluree-db-api/src/graph_query_builder.rs` needs `graph_source_fallback` gated with `#[cfg(feature = \"iceberg\")]` on both the struct field and its constructor initialization. The field is only read inside an `iceberg`-gated fallback path, so leaving it unconditional causes a dead-code warning in default non-iceberg builds." ;
    mem:tag "dead-code" ;
    mem:tag "feature-gating" ;
    mem:tag "fluree-db-api" ;
    mem:tag "graph-query-builder" ;
    mem:tag "iceberg" ;
    mem:tag "r2rml" ;
    mem:tag "warning" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_query_builder.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-27T11:40:37.925049+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmr3thfmbcbwe2fq8hh4ckc7 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Remote binary-index queries can pay repeated leaf-open metadata cost even when decoded leaflet columns are cached: `BinaryIndexStore::open_leaf_handle()` chooses `RangeReadLeafHandle` when the full leaf is not on local disk, and that path re-runs `fetch_header_and_directory()` (range-read header + directory) before `load_columns_cached_via_handle()` can hit `LeafletCache`. Investigating tiny-dataset slow queries should therefore instrument all three layers separately: leaf open, header/directory range reads, and leaflet cache hit/miss." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "instrumentation" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet-cache" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "range-read" ;
    mem:tag "remote-storage" ;
    mem:tag "xray" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/column_loader.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaf_access.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-27T17:00:15.220284+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmrfjybvsfcpabafvy4hecn4 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`BinaryIndexStore::open_leaf_handle()` now caches remote leaf header+directory metadata by `leaf_cid` in-memory before constructing `RangeReadLeafHandle`. This avoids repeating `fetch_header_and_directory()` range reads on repeated opens of the same remote leaf, while leaving column block reads and local full-blob paths unchanged." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "leaf-cache" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "range-read" ;
    mem:tag "remote-storage" ;
    mem:tag "s3" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/format/leaf.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-27T20:25:49.179364+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmrgkcd7aa9aj55j0jseeegb a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "For Lambda query-perf investigations, broad `fluree_db_query=debug` logging is too noisy and the span-heavy join/optional diagnostics can overwhelm trace exports. Prefer `RUST_LOG=info,fluree_db_binary_index=debug` with explicit binary-index debug events (`binary leaf open`, `binary fetched leaf header and directory`, `binary remote range fetch`) to confirm repeated remote opens/downloads and metadata-cache hits." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "cloudwatch" ;
    mem:tag "lambda" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "tracing" ;
    mem:tag "xray" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaf_access.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/optional.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-27T20:43:32.135946+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmrsrnfr06tvkwrwbqmt8w0z a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "PropertyJoinOperator now supports same-subject star blocks that mix variable objects with bound-object existence predicates (for example `?s rdf:type :Deal`, `?s :name ?name`, `?s :stage ?stage`). The operator treats bound-object patterns as existence-only constraints and now captures encoded subject IDs after the first scan so a selective exact scan can drive later batched subject probes even without filter-pushdown object bounds." ;
    mem:tag "batched-probe" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "planner" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "rdf:type" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/planner.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/property_join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-27T23:23:42.456970+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmrwc10tqgrtgqq5j90hqd8k a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "NestedLoopJoinOperator's batched subject-join path now remains enabled when the right pattern has static object bounds, and the batched PSOT scanner applies those bounds row-by-row before materializing bindings. PropertyJoinOperator also now ranks star drivers so bound-object predicates (especially rdf:type) are preferred ahead of range-bounded variable-object predicates when seeding the subject candidate set." ;
    mem:tag "batched-probe" ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "object-bounds" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/property_join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T00:09:14.010238+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmrxf5g1myvt34wg0vf5e6nd a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "PropertyJoinOperator now bypasses per-chunk NestedLoopJoinOperator construction for subject-bound follow-on probes. The star path calls a reusable `batched_subject_probe_binary` helper in `fluree-db-query/src/join.rs` that scans PSOT for a fixed predicate over a bounded subject set, applies optional bound-object or object-range filtering, and returns subject/object matches directly." ;
    mem:tag "batched-probe" ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "psot" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/property_join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T00:28:25.473585+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kms0v33qc3xfxjgj7g8sgje8 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Query-engine cleanup: `fluree-db-query/src/join.rs` now owns shared `make_dict_overlay(ctx, store)` construction for novelty-aware batched probe paths, and `PropertyJoinOperator` factors batched probe plumbing into small helpers (`predicate_sid`, per-predicate bounds/bound-object lookup, probe-match ingestion, driver subject capture). This keeps `PropertyJoinOperator::open` focused on control flow instead of inline setup/details." ;
    mem:tag "cleanup" ;
    mem:tag "dict-overlay" ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "maintainability" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/property_join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T01:27:21.975499+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmt1mrbpkwzyrpfyckbkbkfx a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Object-to-Binding conversion in `fluree-db-query` is centralized in `src/object_binding.rs`. Use `late_materialized_object_binding(...)` for the fast encoded-path mapping from `(o_type,o_key,p_id,t,o_i)` and `materialized_object_binding(...)` for wrapping decoded `FlakeValue`s with the correct `Binding::Sid`/`Binding::Lit` shape and datatype metadata. `binary_scan.rs` and `join.rs` both rely on this helper so blank-node, string/json/vector/NUM_BIG, and literal datatype handling stay aligned." ;
    mem:tag "binding" ;
    mem:tag "cleanup" ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "maintainability" ;
    mem:tag "object-binding" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/object_binding.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T11:00:37.366675+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmt5bw0782hg138vkahvnha3 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Property-join planning now uses a weighted width gate in `fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs`: the star path is only chosen when weighted width > 3.0. Required same-subject triples count as 1.0 each, and immediately trailing same-subject OPTIONAL triples with bound predicates count as 0.5 each. This is a planner-only heuristic; it does not fuse OPTIONAL execution into PropertyJoinOperator, it only influences whether the required block takes the property-join path." ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "planner" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "star-shape" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T12:05:40.487105+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmt5vns3h3p0jvn7taqcfv73 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "PropertyJoinOperator now has a single subject-space follow-on path for binary single-ledger stars: after the first driver predicate seeds encoded subject IDs, it can skip per-predicate PSOT probes and call `batched_subject_star_spot` to walk the SPOT branch once across the candidate subject set, matching multiple remaining predicates and applying bound-object/object-bounds filters before recording per-predicate presence and emitted values. The fast path currently requires all remaining star predicates to have no datatype constraint." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "spot" ;
    mem:tag "star-join" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/property_join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T12:14:18.403921+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmt6z03f41ptyctmg8z6fg37 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Property-join planning/execution now supports a narrow full-star fusion step for single-ledger binary stars: `build_where_operators_seeded_with_needed` can absorb consecutive same-subject single-triple OPTIONALs plus immediately following FILTER/BIND patterns that depend only on required-side vars, and `PropertyJoinOperator` treats those OPTIONAL triples as non-required predicates. Missing fused optional values emit `Binding::Poisoned`, while inline filters/binds run inside property-join row assembly so string predicates like `!STRSTARTS(STR(?stage), \"Closed\")` can execute without leaving the star operator." ;
    mem:tag "filter" ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "spot" ;
    mem:tag "strstarts" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/property_join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T12:33:35.855351+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmt8sf8e55eg6p1cwfx5tgc7 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Zoho CRM query perf snapshot after property-join/star-pass work: local perf improved dramatically on the same dataset — COUNT ~352ms→2ms (~176x), simple 4-property LIMIT query ~8400ms→9ms (~933x), and the full query with OPTIONAL + ORDER BY + FILTER now returns correct filtered results in ~10ms locally. Remote Lambda baseline remained dominated by earlier storage/tracing behavior: original ~27s, remote leaf-open caching brought warm to ~3.0s, and with tracing off current deployed warm stayed ~1.2s. This indicates the recent executor/planner work massively improved local engine cost; remote gains from the newest fused-star/filter path still need fresh Lambda benchmarking." ;
    mem:tag "benchmark" ;
    mem:tag "lambda" ;
    mem:tag "local" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "zoho" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/string.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/property_join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T13:05:31.918535+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmt9rs6m9d4rxt2ges55teq1 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Explain now exposes fused star-path selection. `fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs` centralizes property-join decisioning in `analyze_property_join_plan`, and `fluree-db-query/src/explain.rs::explain_execution_hints()` reuses that logic to report hints like `property_join` and `property_join_fused_star` with counts for required triples, fused optional triples, and inline filter/bind fusion. The API explain response includes these hints under `plan.execution-hints`, even when stats are unavailable." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "explain" ;
    mem:tag "fused-star" ;
    mem:tag "planner" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/query/explain.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/explain.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/explain.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T13:22:37.908659+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmtf7e63dh83atzzsr92t8bx a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Boolean expression caching now has a prepared form for hot filter paths. `fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs` defines `PreparedBoolExpression`, which precomputes the optional cache spec once from an `Expression` and then reuses it across row evaluations. The main repeated filter-bearing operator paths now construct prepared expressions at build time: `FilterOperator`, `HavingOperator`, `InlineOperator::Filter`, and `BindOperator`'s fused post-bind filters. Generic `Expression::eval_to_bool()` still supports uncached ad hoc use, but hot query execution paths no longer re-run cacheability analysis on every row." ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "expression" ;
    mem:tag "filter" ;
    mem:tag "operator" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "prepared" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
