    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_query_builder.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/fluree_ext.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/query.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-08T16:31:01.035691+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01knpz8tevjwyqp67j38nqcwn7 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`fluree iceberg map` remote support uses the generic remote-server path, not tracked-ledger mode. The CLI already had `RemoteLedgerClient::iceberg_map()` and `run_iceberg_map_remote()`; the missing piece was exposing `--remote` on `IcebergMapArgs` and giving it precedence in `run_iceberg_map()`: explicit `--remote` -> `build_remote_client(...)`, else local-server auto-route, else local execution. A focused CLI regression test can prove dispatch by configuring an unreachable remote and asserting the command fails with a remote connection error instead of falling back to local mapping behavior." ;
    mem:tag "cli" ;
    mem:tag "graph-sources" ;
    mem:tag "iceberg" ;
    mem:tag "remote" ;
    mem:tag "remote-client" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/cli/iceberg.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/cli.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/commands/iceberg.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/remote_client.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/tests/integration.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-08T16:37:07.675727+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01knpzk6s59m6z41xhgtqkkw54 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Background index correlation has two paths in `fluree-db-indexer::orchestrator`: (1) preferred copied fields via `IndexRequestCorrelation` (`request_id`, `trace_id`, `operation`) when the caller uses `with_index_request_correlation`; (2) best-effort fallback span context for direct/manual `trigger_index()` callers when no explicit correlation is present. The worker enters the stored fallback span for orchestrator log events so embedded Rust API callers still see span ancestry on background indexer logs, while transaction-triggered server paths continue to rely on copied fields to avoid holding HTTP request spans open." ;
    mem:tag "background-worker" ;
    mem:tag "correlation-id" ;
    mem:tag "indexer" ;
    mem:tag "request-id" ;
    mem:tag "span-context" ;
    mem:tag "tracing" ;
    mem:tag "trigger_index" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/admin.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-indexer/src/orchestrator.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/routes/transact.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-08T16:42:47.973885+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01knpzwv3ahtjn3xz7ksg2a8m9 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "The next Iceberg CLI admin slice is implemented as Iceberg-family wrappers over existing graph-source/server functionality: `fluree iceberg list`, `fluree iceberg info`, and `fluree iceberg drop`. These commands intentionally treat both `Iceberg` and `R2RML` graph source types as part of the Iceberg family because `fluree iceberg map` may create either. `iceberg drop` verifies the target is an Iceberg-family graph source before calling the generic remote/local drop path so it will not accidentally delete a ledger of the same name. Remote execution uses `build_remote_client(...)`, and `RemoteLedgerClient` now has `drop_resource()` for POST `/drop`." ;
    mem:tag "cli" ;
    mem:tag "drop" ;
    mem:tag "graph-sources" ;
    mem:tag "iceberg" ;
    mem:tag "info" ;
    mem:tag "list" ;
    mem:tag "remote" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/cli/iceberg.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/cli.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/commands/iceberg.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/remote_client.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/tests/integration.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-08T16:48:03.690758+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01knq1d8f8prvx6wqghrh5zz9r a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Build-phase index correlation gotcha: wrapping only `fluree-db-indexer::orchestrator` log statements with the stored span is insufficient. The worker must run the entire `build_index_for_record()` future under the stored fallback span, and copied request correlation must be scoped around that future so `build_index_for_record()` can attach `request_id`/`trace_id`/`trigger_operation` to its `index_build` span. Rebuild already propagates `Span::current()` into its top-level `spawn_blocking`, but incremental branch updates needed their own `parent_span.enter()` inside `build/incremental.rs::run_update_branch()`." ;
    mem:tag "background-worker" ;
    mem:tag "correlation-id" ;
    mem:tag "incremental" ;
    mem:tag "indexer" ;
    mem:tag "rebuild" ;
    mem:tag "spawn_blocking" ;
    mem:tag "tracing" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-indexer/src/build/incremental.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-indexer/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-indexer/src/orchestrator.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-08T17:14:30.248574+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01knspnjf2k7s3x6rym31exsn0 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Remote graph source gotchas: graph source records currently only recognize kind types f:IndexSource and f:MappedSource in nameservice parsing, and graph source config is exposed verbatim via nameservice JSON-LD/info output (f:graphSourceConfig). That means a new RemoteSource kind requires storage/file nameservice changes, and bearer tokens or other secrets must not be stored directly in graph source config." ;
    mem:tag "feature-design" ;
    mem:tag "graph-sources" ;
    mem:tag "nameservice" ;
    mem:tag "remote-service" ;
    mem:tag "security" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_info.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-nameservice/src/file.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-nameservice/src/storage_ns.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-09T18:04:31.586698+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kntkdbj9s0akhg36brbre0wa a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Server JSON-LD config support and API Connection JSON-LD are currently two different things. `fluree-db-server`/`fluree server start` only parse top-level `.fluree/config.jsonld` as a serde-friendly config file with a `server` section and ignored `@context`; they do not ingest the API's `Connection`/`Storage`/`Publisher` graph format. Full S3 + split commit/index + DynamoDB nameservice support already exists through `FlureeBuilder::from_json_ld(...).build_client()` / `ConnectionConfig::from_json_ld`, so adding AWS to the server is likely best done by wiring the server to accept a connection JSON-LD source rather than duplicating S3/DynamoDB fields in `ServerConfig`." ;
    mem:tag "aws" ;
    mem:tag "cli" ;
    mem:tag "config" ;
    mem:tag "json-ld" ;
    mem:tag "s3" ;
    mem:tag "server" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/operations/configuration.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/reference/connection-config-jsonld.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-connection/src/config.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/config_file.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/state.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-10T02:26:51.081621+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kp4g1wa8yyty4sd2p03k6bg9 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Strict compact-IRI opt-out wiring has two easy-to-miss edge cases: (1) JSON-LD query `@path` alias extraction currently happens before parse-policy resolution, so `opts.strictCompactIri:false` will not relax undefined-prefix checks inside `@context` `@path` expressions; (2) JSON-LD transaction parse-time `opts` must be stripped before single-object insert/upsert expansion, otherwise `opts` can be treated as normal data because only top-level envelope `@graph` form skips extra keys before expansion." ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "opts" ;
    mem:tag "path-alias" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "strict-compact-iri" ;
    mem:tag "transaction" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/parse/mod.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/parse/policy.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/parse/jsonld.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-graph-json-ld/src/expand.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-13T22:40:33.608461+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:decision-01kkymgaynzn5mrgy21pw22tf6 a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "CLI write command naming: \"transact\" is the umbrella (API builder, HTTP endpoint), while specific operations are \"insert\", \"upsert\", and \"update\". The CLI command is `fluree update` (not `transact`) matching the API's `.transact().update()` pattern. Code: Commands::Update, commands::update::run(), UpdateFormat enum. Remote: update_jsonld()/update_sparql() both route to HTTP /transact. Internal types use \"transact\" for the generic write concept (TransactCore, GraphTransactBuilder, fluree-db-transact crate)." ;
    mem:tag "api-alignment" ;
    mem:tag "cli" ;
    mem:tag "insert" ;
    mem:tag "naming" ;
    mem:tag "taxonomy" ;
    mem:tag "transact" ;
    mem:tag "update" ;
    mem:tag "upsert" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_transact_builder.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/cli.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/commands/update.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/remote_client.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/cli-transact-command" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-17T19:31:31.413037+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "The original CLI command was named `transact` but this conflicted with the established API naming where \"transact\" means any write operation. Renamed to `update` to match the API layer's `.transact().update()` pattern, where update specifically means WHERE/DELETE/INSERT." ;
    mem:alternatives "Keep `transact` as CLI command name (rejected: confuses the umbrella concept with a specific operation type); use `where-delete-insert` or `wdi` (rejected: too verbose/obscure)" .

mem:decision-01kje2pt9maxrxjw49ydgejmpe a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "f:enforceUnique uses storage-layer value identity, NOT RDF strict equality. Key is (graph, predicate, FlakeValue) — ignores RDF datatype IRI and language tag. Same bytes = duplicate regardless of annotation. Different FlakeValue variants (String(\"42\") vs Long(42)) are naturally distinct at storage layer.\n\nUses POST index predicate_object(p, o) without .with_datatype(), matching all datatypes for that (p, o) pair." ;
    mem:tag "FlakeValue" ;
    mem:tag "POST-index" ;
    mem:tag "RDF" ;
    mem:tag "config-graph" ;
    mem:tag "datatype" ;
    mem:tag "enforceUnique" ;
    mem:tag "transact" ;
    mem:tag "uniqueness" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/tx.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/config-graph" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-26T22:56:56.628412+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "RDF strict equality treats \"hello\"^^xsd:string and \"hello\"^^ex:custom as different values because their datatype IRIs differ. For a uniqueness constraint this is surprising and easily subverted — users expect \"same text = same value.\" Storage-layer identity (FlakeValue enum variant + payload) is the right granularity: it's what the index actually stores and compares, it's deterministic, and it prevents accidental or intentional duplicate sneaking via datatype annotation." ;
    mem:alternatives "RDF strict equality (datatype-aware key including dt Sid), datatype-family matching via dt_compatible()" .

mem:fact-01km06dhjzpgyvbs1yc5h0h28e a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Default context: per-ledger JSON prefix map auto-applied to queries/transactions that omit @context. Stored in CAS keyed by ContentId; pointer in ConfigPayload.default_context via nameservice.\n\nPopulation: bulk import captures @prefix + builtins; API set_default_context(); HTTP PUT /v1/fluree/context/*ledger; CLI fluree context set.\n\nPrecedence: Query @context/PREFIX > ledger default > built-in (rdf, rdfs, xsd, owl, sh, geo).\n\nUpdates use CAS via ConfigPublisher::push_config() with retry; disconnect_ledger() evicts cache after update. ProxyNameService does NOT implement ConfigPublisher — context writes only on tx server." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "cas" ;
    mem:tag "cli" ;
    mem:tag "default-context" ;
    mem:tag "http-endpoint" ;
    mem:tag "nameservice" ;
    mem:tag "prefix" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/api/endpoints.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/cli/context.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/concepts/iri-and-context.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/import.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/commands/context_cmd.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-nameservice/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/routes/context.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/default-context" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-18T10:03:48.703812+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjg3zmevnz6mdn53wkqn08p0 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Fluree uses CIDv1 for all content-addressed blobs. Implementation in fluree-db-core/src/content_id.rs wrapping `cid` crate.\n\nFormat: CIDv1 = version(1) + multicodec + multihash(SHA2-256, 32 bytes). Multicodec values in private-use range 0x300000+: Commit(0x300001), Txn(0x300002), IndexRoot(0x300003), IndexBranch/Leaf, DictBlob, Garbage, LedgerConfig, StatsSketch, GraphSourceSnapshot, SpatialIndex.\n\nKey APIs: ContentId::new(kind, bytes) hashes with SHA-256; verify(bytes) re-hashes and compares (NOT valid for commit-v2 which excludes trailing hash+sig); digest_hex() returns 64-char hex; Display uses base32-lower multibase." ;
    mem:tag "CIDv1" ;
    mem:tag "SHA-256" ;
    mem:tag "architecture" ;
    mem:tag "content-id" ;
    mem:tag "content-kind" ;
    mem:tag "multicodec" ;
    mem:tag "multihash" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/content_id.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/content_kind.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/ipfs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-27T17:57:43.003928+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:constraint-01kj8k4mfr2w5h0k2w67w07nz8 a mem:Constraint ;
    mem:content "Important patterns and gotchas:\n- Binary index PSOT range queries may return a SUPERSET of matching flakes — post-filtering by subject/predicate is required (see datalog_rules.rs fix)\n- `spawn_blocking` + `handle.block_on()` pattern in indexer for non-Send types across await points\n- `max_t` tracking in index_build.rs must happen BEFORE retraction skip (op=0) — otherwise retraction-only commits don't update max_t, causing waiter deadlocks" ;
    mem:tag "deadlock" ;
    mem:tag "gotchas" ;
    mem:tag "max-t" ;
    mem:tag "patterns" ;
    mem:tag "post-filtering" ;
    mem:tag "psot" ;
    mem:tag "range-queries" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:severity "must" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-indexer/src/index_build.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/memory" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-24T19:48:40.056044+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kj8k4gvpbtb4njvzqt6tdz1g a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Index pipeline:\n- `build_binary_index()` in fluree-db-indexer/src/lib.rs — direct entry point (takes NsRecord, always builds)\n- `build_index_for_ledger()` — wraps above with nameservice lookup + early-return if current\n- `reindex()` in fluree-db-api/src/admin.rs uses `build_binary_index` for forced rebuilds\n- Old B-tree pipeline fully removed (BatchedRebuild, checkpoints, ReindexProgress, etc.)" ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
