mem:fact-01kqfy6r0w86fcsd9km0707xzg a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "v3 commit envelope reader at `legacy_v3.rs:305-309` deliberately stubs `graph_delta = HashMap::new()` since v3 never encoded the field. Envelope-only walkers (`first_t_where_graph_registered`) therefore return `None` on any chain that includes v3 commits, regardless of whether the named graph was actually registered. Callers that rely on the result for short-circuiting must either fall through to a full load on `None`, detect v3 envelopes and signal \"inconclusive\", or accept silent correctness regressions on legacy chains." ;
    mem:tag "commit-envelope" ;
    mem:tag "gotcha" ;
    mem:tag "graph-delta" ;
    mem:tag "legacy-v3" ;
    mem:tag "short-circuit" ;
    mem:tag "v3-compat" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/indexer_fulltext_provider.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/commit.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/commit/codec/legacy_v3.rs" ;
    mem:branch "fix/reindex-pre-build-perf-regression" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-30T19:35:13.692947+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Surfaced during PR #1211 review — code returned Vec::new() on None even though the PR description said it falls through to full load. Documenting so future envelope-only short-circuit work doesn't repeat the silent-fail shape." .

mem:fact-01kqfy6txdrjppaf6756xzdz25 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`Novelty::bulk_apply_commits` is the O(N log N) bulk replacement for per-commit `apply_commit` on first-load / catch-up paths. Identity sort key is `(s, p, o, dt, m, t, op)`; dedup walk drops an assertion iff the prior kept flake for the same `(s, p, o, dt, m)` was also an assertion (mirrors `fact_currently_asserted_in_graph`). Used by `LedgerState::load_novelty` after reversing HEAD→oldest batches and populating dict_novelty in commit order. Delta vs apply_commit: deduped flakes remain in the FlakeStore arena and self.size over-reports — bounded for fresh-load callers but not appropriate for hot-path mutation." ;
    mem:tag "bulk-apply" ;
    mem:tag "dedup" ;
    mem:tag "indexing" ;
    mem:tag "lambda" ;
    mem:tag "load-novelty" ;
    mem:tag "novelty" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/comparator.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-ledger/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-novelty/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:branch "fix/reindex-pre-build-perf-regression" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-30T19:35:16.653062+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Captures the design contract and arena-bloat semantics from PR #1211 so future callers of bulk_apply_commits don't accidentally wire it into a hot-path mutation site." .

mem:constraint-01kjte29y3cp8mae56xy6yfv2n a mem:Constraint ;
    mem:content "SPARQL↔JSON-LD Parity: both compile to the same IR (fluree-db-query/src/ir.rs) and share the entire execution engine. When adding SPARQL features: (1) shared IR changes already affect JSON-LD — verify JSON-LD tests pass, (2) if expressible in JSON-LD, add parallel tests, (3) execution path missing in JSON-LD lower → track follow-up.\n\nSPARQL tests: it_query_sparql.rs | JSON-LD tests: it_query.rs, it_query_analytical.rs, it_query_grouping.rs\nValidate: `cd testsuite-sparql && make test-eval-cat CAT=<cat>` then `cargo test -p fluree-db-api --test it_query`" ;
    mem:tag "compliance" ;
    mem:tag "constraint" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "must-check" ;
    mem:tag "parity" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "testing" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:severity "must" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_sparql.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/ir.rs" ;
    mem:branch "main" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-03T18:06:20.611062+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjte0r70p5ppv4cjkfyyedpe a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "SPARQL Testsuite critical gotchas:\n- MUST `cd testsuite-sparql/` first — excluded from workspace, `cargo test -p testsuite-sparql` from root FAILS\n- Syntax tests run by default; eval tests need `--include-ignored`\n- Each test runs in subprocess with 5s/10s timeouts — panics show as \"Subprocess error\"\n- W3C data in git submodule `rdf-tests/`; URL→local: strip `https://w3c.github.io/rdf-tests/`, prepend `testsuite-sparql/rdf-tests/`\n- `make investigate` only searches syntax report — use `make investigate-eval` for eval failures\n- Key commands: `make count-eval`, `make test-eval-cat CAT=functions`, `make summary`, `make classify`" ;
    mem:tag "commands" ;
    mem:tag "compliance" ;
    mem:tag "gotchas" ;
    mem:tag "testing" ;
    mem:tag "testsuite-sparql" ;
    mem:tag "w3c" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "Cargo.toml" ;
    mem:artifactRef "testsuite-sparql/Cargo.toml" ;
    mem:artifactRef "testsuite-sparql/Makefile" ;
    mem:artifactRef "testsuite-sparql/tests/w3c_sparql.rs" ;
    mem:branch "main" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-03T18:05:29.696388+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjte1yw4jyrqvnpq27mr2m9v a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "SPARQL and JSON-LD queries compile to the same IR and execute on the same engine.\n\nCompilation: SPARQL via fluree-db-sparql/src/lower/ → IR; JSON-LD via fluree-db-query/src/parse/ → same IR. Convergence at view/query.rs → build_executable_for_view() → execute_view_internal().\n\nShared: Expression enum (66+ functions), AggregateFn enum, Pattern enum (Triple, Optional, Minus, Union, etc.), IriEncoder trait.\n\nSPARQL-only: property path lowering, RDF-star, ASK form, SPARQL Update, dataset clause validation." ;
    mem:tag "architecture" ;
    mem:tag "ir" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "parity" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "shared-execution" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/aggregate.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/ir.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/parse/lower.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/lower/" ;
    mem:branch "main" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-03T18:06:09.284115+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:constraint-01kp8yczz09ndt54ztchbheeyb a mem:Constraint ;
    mem:content "JSON-LD transaction parsing does NOT auto-promote bare string values to IRI references. User data becomes an IRI only when wrapped in `{\"@id\": \"...\"}` or when the property has `@type: \"@id\"` in `@context`. The former `looks_like_iri` heuristic (three sites in parse/jsonld.rs) was removed — it silently promoted strings starting with `http://`/`https://`/`did:`/`fluree:`/`urn:` to IRIs, which violated the JSON-LD spec (especially for `{\"@value\": \"...\"}`, explicitly a literal)." ;
    mem:tag "iri" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "parsing" ;
    mem:tag "spec-compliance" ;
    mem:tag "transactions" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:severity "must" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/concepts/iri-and-context.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/parse/jsonld.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-graph-json-ld/src/iri.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-15T16:08:15.584179+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Prevents silent data corruption: a literal like `{\"@value\": \"urn:isbn:123\"}` must round-trip as a string. Distinct from the strict compact-IRI GUARD (check_unresolved_iri) which stays — that runs only in IRI positions (@id, @type, predicate, datatype) and errors on unresolved prefixes rather than guessing." .

mem:decision-01kp938r33m9e5fzksf47hcfgc a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "For a future batched query API, the primary use case is independent page-view reads, not ordered multi-step execution. Same-t guarantees should be cheap and strong for same-ledger batches by reusing one resolved view/handle; federated or multi-ledger batches may need extra per-source time resolution and should not promise the same semantics by default." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "batch" ;
    mem:tag "federation" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "time-travel" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/query/bm25.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/dataset_query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/query.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-15T17:33:19.331308+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Captures the preferred semantics for batch query design so future API work does not overfit SQL-style transactions or overpromise cross-ledger consistency." .

mem:decision-01kpkj2j3jyq7742agn0yfhpsy a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "For planned fulltext config support, unrelated traffic should stay cheap: precompute `FulltextHookConfig` once per indexing run, keep `FulltextHook::on_op` scalar-only for reject paths, and only build/attach fulltext provider/config maps for queries whose compiled IR actually contains `fulltext(...)`." ;
    mem:tag "config" ;
    mem:tag "fulltext" ;
    mem:tag "indexer" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "FULLTEXT_CONFIG.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/dataset_query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-indexer/src/fulltext_hook.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-19T19:04:29.554332+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This isolates the feature's cost to fulltext-relevant writes and queries, avoiding accidental overhead on unrelated transactions and query setup." .

mem:fact-01kp4rwg9hcyj1ypqmfmygdxym a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Strict compact-IRI policy: as of commit 170bccc9, JSON-LD transactions default `strict_compact_iri=true`. Any compact IRI (e.g. `rdf:JSON`, `xsd:string`, `ex:name`) used in data/query/update must have its prefix declared in `@context`, otherwise parsing returns `UnresolvedCompactIri`. The former PR #148 \"Layer 2 fallback\" for well-known prefixes (rdf:, xsd:) is gone. When tests fail with `UnresolvedCompactIri`, fix is to add the prefix to the test's explicit `@context` (per user preference: never rely on default/implicit context in tests). Override via `opts.strict_compact_iri = false` or JSON `opts: {strictCompactIri: false}` if legacy behavior required." ;
    mem:tag "json-ld" ;
    mem:tag "parse" ;
    mem:tag "strict-compact-iri" ;
    mem:tag "testing" ;
    mem:tag "transact" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/parse/policy.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/parse/jsonld.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-14T01:14:54.641170+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kp4rwsy7pf6999h00kv3wdcg a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Rebase: before replay, branch nameservice head must be reset to source head via nameservice.reset_head(). replay_commit uses CommitOpts with skip_sequencing → fast_forward_commit CAS path requiring strictly increasing t. Without reset, replaying at t=N+1 collides with pre-rebase head, producing PublishLostRace.\n\nMerge: fast-forward CAS rejects \"already up to date\" cases (same head_id at same t). merge_branch_inner now short-circuits when target_head == source_head_id and returns no-op MergeReport." ;
    mem:tag "branches" ;
    mem:tag "cas" ;
    mem:tag "fast-forward" ;
    mem:tag "merge" ;
    mem:tag "nameservice" ;
    mem:tag "rebase" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/merge.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/rebase.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/commit.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-14T01:15:04.519020+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kp4rwyr6eas353wf1fwn2431 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Nextest SIGABRTs in fluree-db-server integration/policy/proxy/oidc tests when running multiple crates in parallel on macOS are resource contention, NOT test logic bugs. Running `cargo nextest run -p fluree-db-server --all-features` alone passes all 204 tests; running alongside fluree-db-api in the same invocation causes ~37 SIGABRTs at 0.05–0.6s (pre-body). `--test-threads=4` also makes them pass. When you see SIGABRT en-masse in server tests during a workspace run, isolate to the single crate before assuming a bug." ;
    mem:tag "ci" ;
    mem:tag "macos" ;
    mem:tag "nextest" ;
    mem:tag "parallelism" ;
    mem:tag "sigabrt" ;
    mem:tag "testing" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-14T01:15:09.446809+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kp8psqsjk2g8zke4trn7ryck a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "A duplicate-subject symptom after reindexing old commits (for example `?s rdf:type Class` returning the same subject twice after delete-then-reinsert) most plausibly comes from legacy transaction commits, not PSOT scanning itself: old wildcard-delete / upsert paths could persist ineffective retracts for indexed facts, and rebuild only dedups exact V2 identity `(s,p,o_type,o_key,o_i)`, so mismatched legacy retracts leave the original assert alive and a later reinsert adds a second live row." ;
    mem:tag "datatype" ;
    mem:tag "duplicates" ;
    mem:tag "legacy-commits" ;
    mem:tag "psot" ;
    mem:tag "reindex" ;
    mem:tag "upsert" ;
    mem:tag "wildcard-delete" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_transact_update.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_update_wildcard_delete_indexed.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-indexer/src/run_index/build/merge.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/stage.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-15T13:55:24.594356+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This links a user-visible duplicate-query symptom to the historical write-path bugs and the rebuild identity rules, which is useful context for future investigations." .

mem:fact-01kp8y8sj2452zvzzpexfrnvep a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Transaction staging currently buffers WHERE results multiple times: query execution returns `Vec<Batch>`, `stage.rs` merges them into one `Batch`, then `materialize_encoded_bindings_for_txn` clones again into a fully materialized `Batch` before flake generation. Large DELETE/UPDATE WHERE operations can therefore pay ~2-3 full copies of binding memory before any cancellation/dedup happens." ;
    mem:tag "batch" ;
    mem:tag "memory" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "stage" ;
    mem:tag "transact" ;
    mem:tag "update" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binding.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/stage.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-15T16:05:57.954523+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is a recurring memory hotspot for large update/delete transactions and should be recalled before doing staging performance work." .

mem:fact-01kpdqtnax7zn3twyyn50xxwmz a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Fuel tracking gotcha: `BinaryScanOperator::batch_to_bindings` now attaches a tracker-aware `BinaryGraphView`, but dict-touch fuel exhaustion from `resolve_subject_iri` / `resolve_subject_sid` / `decode_value` is still mapped to `QueryError::Internal` instead of `FuelLimitExceeded`. Separately, `ExecutionContext::graph_view()` does not attach `ctx.tracker`, so late-materialization helpers that go through `ctx.resolve_subject_iri()` / `decode_encoded_value()` bypass the new dict-touch charging entirely." ;
    mem:tag "binary-scan" ;
    mem:tag "dict-touch" ;
    mem:tag "fuel" ;
    mem:tag "late-materialization" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "tracking" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/context.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-17T12:49:35.582316+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Future work on fuel accounting needs to preserve proper FuelExceeded propagation and avoid underbilling in late-materialized query paths." .

mem:fact-01kpehw5sdpvgc26bxg5jthh2s a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Lambda/query warmup currently overpromises dict warming: `fluree-db-server` calls `BinaryIndexStore::preload_dict_leaves()` during preload, but that method is still a TODO returning `Ok(0)`. Also, duplicate remote fetch prevention is asymmetric: dict leaves use `LeafletCache::try_get_or_load_dict_leaf` single-flight, but generic artifact-cache/leaf open paths do not coalesce concurrent cold misses, so the same CID can still be fetched from remote multiple times under concurrency." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "lambda" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "s3" ;
    mem:tag "warmup" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/artifact_cache.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-17T20:24:48.173473+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is an easy-to-miss reason warm Lambdas may not improve much and why duplicated S3 reads can still happen even though some cache layers exist." .

mem:fact-01kpepmqtapmksm216fde5jv75 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "The fused fast path for `COUNT(DISTINCT ?o)` with an existence-only same-subject join is intended for `?s <p_count> ?o1 . ?s <p_exists> ?o2`, and it must be order-insensitive. If detection only checks the first triple for the counted object var, queries like `?s a Person . ?s sourceLink ?link` fall back to the generic nested-loop join plan even though they match the fast-path shape." ;
    mem:tag "count-distinct" ;
    mem:tag "fast-path" ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "planner" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/operator_tree.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-17T21:48:07.370571+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This planner gotcha is subtle and directly affects Lambda perf investigations for same-subject COUNT(DISTINCT) queries." .

mem:fact-01kpery4cg5x0sz1w9b3dzbdnp a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`NestedLoopJoinOperator` can batch subject-bound fixed-object existence probes like `(?s, fixed_p, fixed_o)` by reusing `batched_subject_probe_binary` with `bound_object` and `emit_object=false`; the prior slowdown came from this shape missing `batched_eligible`, not from `active_graph_mode=many`." ;
    mem:tag "batched-probe" ;
    mem:tag "existence" ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-17T22:28:12.304782+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is a non-obvious planner/operator capability gap that explains repeated NLJ opens on warm runs and is worth recalling before future query-perf debugging." .

mem:fact-01kpf4qqbhbwvve54zr565y379 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`fluree-db-query/src/join.rs` now keeps per-join path-selection logs (`opened nested loop join`, `nested loop join runtime path`) at `trace`, while `join batched existence flush complete` only stays at `debug` for slow flushes (>=10ms) or non-trivial batches (accum_len >= 8). This avoids CloudWatch floods during Lambda perf captures." ;
    mem:tag "join" ;
    mem:tag "lambda" ;
    mem:tag "logging" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "tracing" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-18T01:54:25.265596+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "The previous debug-level join diagnostics produced hundreds of MB of logs and obscured the useful bottleneck signals." .

mem:fact-01kpg3c19kb0nmez28863spr69 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Low-noise Q2 perf diagnostics now live in `fluree-db-query/src/optional.rs` and `fluree-db-query/src/sort.rs`: `optional batch summary` logs at debug only for expensive batches (>=25ms or >=8 builds/cache hits/result batches), and `sort blocking summary` logs at debug only for non-trivial blocking sorts (>=25ms or >=1000 input rows). The old per-row correlated-OPTIONAL planning log is now trace-level." ;
    mem:tag "logging" ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "sort" ;
    mem:tag "tracing" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/optional.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/sort.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-18T10:49:48.083428+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This keeps CloudWatch captures small while still surfacing the likely remaining Q2 hotspots." .

mem:fact-01kpg6gdmx8k7zcqyh5byw88dn a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`PatternOptionalBuilder` now has a batched execution path for single-triple correlated OPTIONALs with a subject bound from the left, a fixed predicate, no datatype constraint, and single-ledger binary execution. `OptionalOperator` asks builders for a batch result first, so queries with repeated `OPTIONAL { ?s <p> ?o }` clauses can probe many left-side subjects at once instead of opening one scan per row." ;
    mem:tag "batched-probe" ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "planner" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "tracing" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/optional.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-18T11:44:37.533439+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is a generic executor optimization for a common OPTIONAL shape, not a dataset-specific fast path." .

mem:fact-01kpg89x3hs343017xzq1cgbj0 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`build_where_operators_seeded_with_needed` can now coalesce consecutive single-triple OPTIONALs into one `GroupedPatternOptionalBuilder` when they share the same already-bound subject var, use bound predicates, have no datatype constraint, and introduce distinct optional-only object vars. The grouped builder batches all predicates for the current required batch via `batched_subject_probe_binary`, removing left-deep OPTIONAL drain without tying the optimization to any specific query or dataset." ;
    mem:tag "batched-probe" ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "planner" ;
    mem:tag "property-join" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/where_plan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/optional.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-18T12:16:01.137157+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is the generic follow-on to the batched single-triple OPTIONAL work and explains why consecutive OPTIONAL chains can speed up substantially." .

mem:fact-01kpga78m373fmr7hmsy4a7a0t a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`UnionOperator` preserves correlated UNION semantics by executing each branch per input row and buffering branch output batches row-by-row, so downstream operators can see severe batch fragmentation even when the union's child produced large batches. For Q2-style reasoning-expanded unions, this can starve `GroupedPatternOptionalBuilder` and make its batched path observe `rows_considered = 1` repeatedly." ;
    mem:tag "batching" ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "reasoning" ;
    mem:tag "union" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/optional.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/union.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-18T12:49:31.779188+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is a non-obvious executor interaction that matters for future batching fixes upstream of grouped OPTIONALs." .

mem:fact-01kpgbv82fg78tjqhhptx05tvz a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`UnionOperator` now buffers correlated branch results until it can emit a full downstream batch (or true exhaustion), rather than returning after the first per-row fragment. That preserves UNION semantics but prevents reasoning-expanded unions from starving downstream operators like grouped OPTIONAL and sort with one-row batches." ;
    mem:tag "batching" ;
    mem:tag "optional" ;
    mem:tag "query-perf" ;
    mem:tag "sort" ;
    mem:tag "union" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/union.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-18T13:17:55.151538+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This batching invariant is non-obvious and directly explains why the generic fix speeds up UNION-heavy queries without being dataset-specific." .

mem:fact-01kpkzmffzgmf6h67prn8j3hd3 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "SHACL config currently parses `f:shapesSource` into `ShaclDefaults`, but transaction-time engine construction ignores it and always compiles shapes from `ledger.as_graph_db_ref(0)` / `g_id=0`. Docs that describe named-graph shapes sources are ahead of the implementation today." ;
    mem:tag "config-graph" ;
    mem:tag "docs-gap" ;
    mem:tag "shacl" ;
    mem:tag "shapessource" ;
    mem:tag "validation" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/guides/cookbook-shacl.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/ledger-config/setting-groups.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/config_resolver.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/tx.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-shacl/src/compile.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-19T23:01:28.191644+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Future SHACL or config work needs this recalled up front because it creates a silent mismatch between documented configuration and actual validation behavior." .

mem:fact-01kpkzmkq2abxas9h48h6k21p6 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Transaction-time SHACL validation only discovers applicable shapes through the cache indexes for `sh:targetNode` and `sh:targetClass`; `sh:targetSubjectsOf` and `sh:targetObjectsOf` are compiled but not indexed, so staged-subject validation can silently skip those shapes even though full `validate_all()` handles them." ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "shacl" ;
    mem:tag "targets" ;
    mem:tag "transaction-validation" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-shacl/src/cache.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-shacl/src/compile.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-shacl/src/validate.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-19T23:01:32.514812+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is an easy-to-miss correctness bug because the target predicates look implemented in the compiler but do not actually fire in the main transact path." .

mem:fact-01kpm204vw7pj6e9hbag009d2d a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Ledger config parses `f:schemaSource` and `f:rulesSource`, but query-time reasoning currently ignores them: OWL2 RL ontology scans and `f:rule` extraction run against the queried `GraphDbRef`'s `g_id`. In `compute_derived_facts`, OWL-derived overlay flakes are also emitted only under graph id 0." ;
    mem:tag "config-graph" ;
    mem:tag "datalog" ;
    mem:tag "named-graph" ;
    mem:tag "owl2rl" ;
    mem:tag "reasoning" ;
    mem:tag "rulessource" ;
    mem:tag "schemasource" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/config_resolver.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/graph_db_ref.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/ledger_config.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/datalog_rules.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/reasoning_prep.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-19T23:42:47.676059+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Future reasoning/config work could otherwise assume named-graph schema/rule sources are already honored, because docs and config structs expose those fields even though runtime still scopes to the query graph/default derived overlay." .

mem:fact-01kpm3sz8pxzakzcj4r8xx687v a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "OWL restriction evaluation for chain-valued `owl:onProperty` must traverse the union of the current delta and accumulated derived facts. Evaluating chain hops against delta and derived separately misses mixed paths like `delta(P1)` followed by `derived(P2)` in the same fixpoint iteration." ;
    mem:tag "fixpoint" ;
    mem:tag "owl2rl" ;
    mem:tag "property-chain" ;
    mem:tag "reasoner" ;
    mem:tag "restrictions" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-reasoner/src/execute/restriction_rules.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-reasoner/src/execute/tests/restriction_rule_tests.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-20T00:14:22.486023+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "This is a subtle semi-naive reasoning invariant; future restriction or chain work could easily reintroduce the bug by splitting lookups across delta and derived." .
